OL,3,CWoman struck by tree being felled left
OL,4,Cwith traumatic brain injury
OL,6,FA woman who was struck by a tree that
OL,7,Fwas being felled in East Sussex says
OL,8,Fshe has lost her independence after
OL,9,Fsuffering a traumatic brain injury.
OL,11,FCaroline Leafe, 70, was walking along
OL,12,Fa deer track in Ashdown Forest with
OL,13,Fher husband, Ken, and their dog,
OL,14,FMonty, when the pair were hit by a
OL,15,Fsilver birch tree that was being
OL,16,Ffelled on January 25 2023.
OL,18,FThe Conservators of Ashdown Forest,
OL,19,Fthe body that manages Ashdown Forest,
OL,20,Fhad found the 12-metre tree was
OL,21,Frotting and needed to be cut down.
