OL,3,CWoman struck by tree being felled left
OL,4,Cwith traumatic brain injury
OL,6,FThe tree, in the corner of Broadstone
OL,7,FCar Park, was surrounded by public
OL,8,Ffootpaths, including the main pathway
OL,9,Fto the visitor centre.
OL,11,FA forest ranger made a cut with a
OL,12,Fchainsaw and the tree began to fall.
OL,13,FThe ranger noticed Mr and Mrs Leafe
OL,14,Fwalking on the nearby deer track and
OL,15,Fattempted to warn them but it was too
OL,16,Flate.
OL,18,FMrs Leafe suffered a traumatic brain
OL,19,Finjury, a fractured collar bone,
OL,20,Fseveral fractured ribs and a shoulder
OL,21,Fdislocation.
