OL,3,CWoman struck by tree being felled left
OL,4,Cwith traumatic brain injury
OL,6,FShe spent a considerable amount of
OL,7,Ftime in hospital following the
OL,8,Fincident and continues to have
OL,9,Fphysical and cognitive therapy. She
OL,10,Falso had to surrender her driving
OL,11,Flicence but can now drive again.
OL,13,FShe said she's "suffered a loss of
OL,14,Findependence" with Ken having to offer
OL,15,Fher a lot more support.
OL,17,FShe added: "The head injuries included
OL,18,Fspeech problems and emotional problems.
