OL,3,CWoman struck by tree being felled left
OL,4,Cwith traumatic brain injury
OL,6,FIt meant precautions such as posting
OL,7,Fwarning signs and using barriers were
OL,8,Fnot put in place to prevent members of
OL,9,Fthe public from accessing areas where
OL,10,Fthe tree felling was taking place.
OL,12,FThe Conservators of Ashdown Forest
OL,13,Fpleaded guilty to breaching Section
OL,14,F3(1) of the Health and Safety at Work
OL,15,Fetc. Act 1974. The trust was fined
OL,16,F#8,000 and ordered to pay #3,589.80 in
OL,17,Fcosts.
